cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new internal Hilbert-style axiomatisation for separation logic, which is a logical system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as separation logic is a formalism used in programming language semantics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as separation logic is used in program verification and software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the expressive power of the new logic. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents a new approach to axiomatise separation logics.
